cache/generation/prose_review/prompts/accessibility-highlight-overlay.json:170:  "rendered_prompt": "You are reviewing an existing DALi dali-ui application developer guide draft.\nThis is Phase 2.3.5: source-grounded prose review.\n\nPrimary goal:\n- Improve natural-language accuracy and guide flow using repository evidence.\n- Preserve the document's useful structure and examples whenever possible.\n- Do not perform a full rewrite.\n- Keep the revised user-facing guide in en only.\n- Remove Korean, Japanese, Chinese, or other non-English prose from the revised guide.\n\nFeature target:\n- Feature: Accessibility Highlight Overlay (accessibility-highlight-overlay)\n- Category: accessibility\n- Guide profile: dali-ui-app\n- Audience: application developers using dali-ui public APIs\n\nReview rules:\n- Review every natural-language paragraph line by line against public headers, implementation files, samples, and UTCs when needed.\n- Accuracy is the first priority. Flow is the second priority.\n- Edit the smallest unit needed: word, sentence, paragraph, or section-local addition/removal.\n- If a word-level change is enough, change only the word.\n- If a sentence-level change is enough, change only the sentence.\n- If an entire paragraph is based on a wrong premise, revise, add, or remove that paragraph.\n- Preserve code blocks when possible.\n- If prose can be corrected to match an already accurate code block, prefer changing prose.\n- If the code block itself makes the prose inaccurate or breaks the guide flow, rewrite only the smallest necessary part of that code block and verify it against public headers/source.\n- Do not invent APIs.\n- Do not add generic filler just to make the document longer.\n- Do not change section structure unless prose_review.allow_section_restructure is true or the current prose is clearly misleading.\n- Prefer localized edits when prose_review.localized_edits_only is true.\n- Preserve code blocks especially when prose_review.preserve_code_blocks is true.\n- Prefer Dali::Ui::View, typed setters, fluent chaining, and view-tree idioms for app-facing guidance.\n- Treat dali-core and dali-adaptor APIs as reference/context unless the feature explicitly requires them.\n\nContext summary:\n{\n  \"content_quality\": {\n    \"overview_style\": \"very_short\",\n    \"require_table_of_contents\": true,\n    \"require_rich_api_examples\": true,\n    \"require_backticks_for_api_names\": true,\n    \"topic_sections_must_be_feature_specific\": true,\n    \"avoid_mechanical_api_listing\": true,\n    \"default_object_model\": \"Use Dali::Ui::View rather than Dali::Actor for app-facing object examples.\",\n    \"guide_assumption\": \"The reader is using dali-ui to build applications.\"\n  },\n  \"prose_review\": {\n    \"enabled\": true,\n    \"apply_to\": \"all\",\n    \"preserve_code_blocks\": true,\n    \"localized_edits_only\": true,\n    \"allow_section_restructure\": false,\n    \"output_review_report\": true,\n    \"fail_open_on_parse_error\": true\n  },\n  \"surface_usage\": {\n    \"primary_surface\": \"dali-ui\",\n    \"rules\": [\n      \"Use dali-ui symbols as the app-facing API surface.\",\n      \"Use dali-core and dali-adaptor symbols only as setup/background unless the usage pattern explicitly marks them preferred.\",\n      \"Prefer View-based examples over raw Actor object-model examples.\"\n    ],\n    \"symbol_counts\": {\n      \"dali-ui\": 8\n    }\n  },\n  \"usage_patterns\": [\n    {\n      \"avoid_symbols\": [],\n      \"confidence\": 0.85,\n      \"id\": \"accessibility-highlight-overlay_basic_setup\",\n      \"intent\": \"Create and configure the primary object using public dali-ui APIs.\",\n      \"preferred_symbols\": [\n        \"Dali::Ui::AccessibilityHighlightOverlay::SetCustomHighlight\",\n        \"Dali::Ui::AccessibilityHighlightOverlay::SetOverlayMode\"\n      ],\n      \"property_values\": [],\n      \"source\": \"feature_owned_public_api\",\n      \"usage_note\": \"Prefer typed constructors and setters when available.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"allowed_symbols_sample\": [\n    {\n      \"display_name\": \"AccessibilityHighlightOverlay\",\n      \"header_path\": \"repos/dali-ui/dali-ui-foundation/integration-api/accessibility-highlight-overlay.h\",\n      \"kind\": \"class\",\n      \"public_api\": true,\n      \"signature\": \"Dali::Ui::AccessibilityHighlightOverlay\",\n      \"surface\": \"dali-ui\",\n      \"symbol_id\": \"Dali::Ui::AccessibilityHighlightOverlay\",\n      \"usage_scope\": \"primary\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"display_name\": \"AccessibilityHighlightOverlay\",\n      \"header_path\": \"repos/dali-ui/dali-ui-foundation/integration-api/accessibility-highlight-overlay.h\",\n      \"kind\": \"constructor\",\n      \"public_api\": true,\n      \"signature\": \"AccessibilityHighlightOverlay()\",\n      \"surface\": \"dali-ui\",\n      \"symbol_id\": \"Dali::Ui::AccessibilityHighlightOverlay::AccessibilityHighlightOverlay\",\n      \"usage_scope\": \"primary_member\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"display_name\": \"GetOverlayMode\",\n      \"header_path\": \"repos/dali-ui/dali-ui-foundation/integration-api/accessibility-highlight-overlay.h\",\n      \"kind\": \"method\",\n      \"public_api\": true,\n      \"signature\": \"OverlayHighlightMode GetOverlayMode() const\",\n      \"surface\": \"dali-ui\",\n      \"symbol_id\": \"Dali::Ui::AccessibilityHighlightOverlay::GetOverlayMode\",\n      \"usage_scope\": \"primary_member\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"display_name\": \"HideOverlay\",\n      \"header_path\": \"repos/dali-ui/dali-ui-foundation/integration-api/accessibility-highlight-overlay.h\",\n      \"kind\": \"method\",\n      \"public_api\": true,\n      \"signature\": \"void HideOverlay()\",\n      \"surface\": \"dali-ui\",\n      \"symbol_id\": \"Dali::Ui::AccessibilityHighlightOverlay::HideOverlay\",\n      \"usage_scope\": \"primary_member\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"display_name\": \"ResetCustomHighlight\",\n      \"header_path\": \"repos/dali-ui/dali-ui-foundation/integration-api/accessibility-highlight-overlay.h\",\n      \"kind\": \"method\",\n      \"public_api\": true,\n      \"signature\": \"void ResetCustomHighlight()\",\n      \"surface\": \"dali-ui\",\n      \"symbol_id\": \"Dali::Ui::AccessibilityHighlightOverlay::ResetCustomHighlight\",\n      \"usage_scope\": \"primary_member\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"display_name\": \"SetCustomHighlight\",\n      \"header_path\": \"repos/dali-ui/dali-ui-foundation/integration-api/accessibility-highlight-overlay.h\",\n      \"kind\": \"method\",\n      \"public_api\": true,\n      \"signature\": \"void SetCustomHighlight(Vector2 position, Vector2 size)\",\n      \"surface\": \"dali-ui\",\n      \"symbol_id\": \"Dali::Ui::AccessibilityHighlightOverlay::SetCustomHighlight\",\n      \"usage_scope\": \"primary_member\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"display_name\": \"SetOverlayMode\",\n      \"header_path\": \"repos/dali-ui/dali-ui-foundation/integration-api/accessibility-highlight-overlay.h\",\n      \"kind\": \"method\",\n      \"public_api\": true,\n      \"signature\": \"void SetOverlayMode(OverlayHighlightMode mode)\",\n      \"surface\": \"dali-ui\",\n      \"symbol_id\": \"Dali::Ui::AccessibilityHighlightOverlay::SetOverlayMode\",\n      \"usage_scope\": \"primary_member\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"display_name\": \"UpdateOverlay\",\n      \"header_path\": \"repos/dali-ui/dali-ui-foundation/integration-api/accessibility-highlight-overlay.h\",\n      \"kind\": \"method\",\n      \"public_api\": true,\n      \"signature\": \"void UpdateOverlay(Dali::Actor &activeHighlight)\",\n      \"surface\": \"dali-ui\",\n      \"symbol_id\": \"Dali::Ui::AccessibilityHighlightOverlay::UpdateOverlay\",\n      \"usage_scope\": \"primary_member\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"property_owners_sample\": [],\n  \"example_candidates\": [],\n  \"draft_path\": \"cache/generation/drafts/accessibility-highlight-overlay.md\",\n  \"context_pack_path\": \"cache/generation/context_packs/accessibility-highlight-overlay.json\"\n}\n\nOutput contract:\n- Put the revised full Markdown between -----BEGIN_REVISED_MARKDOWN----- and -----END_REVISED_MARKDOWN-----.\n- Put the concise prose review report between -----BEGIN_PROSE_REVIEW_REPORT----- and -----END_PROSE_REVIEW_REPORT-----.\n- Do not include commentary outside those markers.\n- Do not wrap the revised Markdown in a code fence.\n- Inside the Markdown markers, output the complete final Markdown document only.\n- If no prose changes are needed, put the full unchanged original Markdown between the Markdown markers.\n- Do not replace the Markdown marker content with status commentary such as 'already valid', 'no changes needed', or 'review complete'.\n- The first non-frontmatter content inside the Markdown markers must be the top-level document title heading.\n- The review report should list changed prose, source evidence, and remaining concerns.\n\n-----BEGIN_REVISED_MARKDOWN-----\n<revised full markdown here>\n-----END_REVISED_MARKDOWN-----\n-----BEGIN_PROSE_REVIEW_REPORT-----\n# <Feature> Prose Review\n...\n-----END_PROSE_REVIEW_REPORT-----\n\nOriginal Markdown draft:\n---\ntitle: Accessibility Highlight Overlay\nsidebar_label: Accessibility Highlight Overlay\ncategory: accessibility\n---\n\n# Accessibility Highlight Overlay\n\n`Dali::Ui::AccessibilityHighlightOverlay` controls the visual highlight rectangle used to show the current accessibility focus in a dali-ui application.\n\n## Table of Contents\n\n- [Create and Configure the Overlay](#create-and-configure-the-overlay)\n- [Use a Custom Highlight Rectangle](#use-a-custom-highlight-rectangle)\n- [Update and Hide the Highlight](#update-and-hide-the-highlight)\n- [Restore Default Highlight Behavior](#restore-default-highlight-behavior)\n\n## Create and Configure the Overlay\n\nCreate `Dali::Ui::AccessibilityHighlightOverlay` as the application-level object that owns highlight overlay behavior. The overlay mode is configured with `SetOverlayMode()`, and the current mode can be read back with `GetOverlayMode()`.\n\nWhen your application stores the preferred mode elsewhere, pass that mode into the overlay rather than hard-coding accessibility behavior in individual views.\n\n```cpp\nvoid ApplyAccessibilityHighlightMode(\n  Dali::Ui::AccessibilityHighlightOverlay& overlay,\n  decltype(overlay.GetOverlayMode()) mode)\n{\n  overlay.SetOverlayMode(mode);\n}\n\nvoid PreserveCurrentAccessibilityHighlightMode(\n  Dali::Ui::AccessibilityHighlightOverlay& overlay)\n{\n  auto currentMode = overlay.GetOverlayMode();\n  overlay.SetOverlayMode(currentMode);\n}\n```\n\nFor simple ownership, construct the overlay with `AccessibilityHighlightOverlay()` and keep it near the dali-ui view coordination code that handles accessibility focus changes.\n\n```cpp\nclass AccessibilityHighlightController\n{\npublic:\n  AccessibilityHighlightController() = default;\n\n  void SetMode(decltype(mOverlay.GetOverlayMode()) mode)\n  {\n    mOverlay.SetOverlayMode(mode);\n  }\n\n  decltype(mOverlay.GetOverlayMode()) GetMode() const\n  {\n    return mOverlay.GetOverlayMode();\n  }\n\nprivate:\n  Dali::Ui::AccessibilityHighlightOverlay mOverlay;\n};\n```\n\n## Use a Custom Highlight Rectangle\n\nUse `SetCustomHighlight()` when the visible highlight should be drawn around a specific rectangle instead of the overlay's default target bounds. The rectangle is described by a position and size.\n\nThis is useful when a dali-ui view presents a composite control and the accessible focus should cover only the meaningful interactive region.\n\n```cpp\nvoid HighlightRegion(\n  Dali::Ui::AccessibilityHighlightOverlay& overlay,\n  Dali::Vector2 position,\n  Dali::Vector2 size)\n{\n  overlay.SetCustomHighlight(position, size);\n}\n```\n\nA controller can keep this operation close to the app-facing dali-ui view logic, while still letting `Dali::Ui::AccessibilityHighlightOverlay` own the overlay state.\n\n```cpp\nclass FocusHighlightPresenter\n{\npublic:\n  void ShowCustomFocusBounds(Dali::Vector2 topLeft, Dali::Vector2 dimensions)\n  {\n    mOverlay.SetCustomHighlight(topLeft, dimensions);\n  }\n\n  void UseConfiguredMode(decltype(mOverlay.GetOverlayMode()) mode)\n  {\n    mOverlay.SetOverlayMode(mode);\n  }\n\nprivate:\n  Dali::Ui::AccessibilityHighlightOverlay mOverlay;\n};\n```\n\n## Update and Hide the Highlight\n\n`UpdateOverlay()` updates the overlay from the current accessibility highlight target. In a dali-ui application, treat this as the bridge point from your focused `Dali::Ui::View` coordination code into the overlay update path. The public signature accepts the active highlight target by reference.\n\nUse `HideOverlay()` when the app should remove the accessibility highlight, such as when focus leaves the active view area or when the accessibility focus state is cleared.\n\n```cpp\nvoid RefreshAccessibilityHighlight(\n  Dali::Ui::AccessibilityHighlightOverlay& overlay,\n  Dali::Actor& activeHighlight)\n{\n  overlay.UpdateOverlay(activeHighlight);\n}\n\nvoid ClearAccessibilityHighlight(Dali::Ui::AccessibilityHighlightOverlay& overlay)\n{\n  overlay.HideOverlay();\n}\n```\n\nA small wrapper keeps the update and hide decisions centralized.\n\n```cpp\nclass AccessibilityFocusOverlay\n{\npublic:\n  void Update(Dali::Actor& activeHighlight)\n  {\n    mOverlay.UpdateOverlay(activeHighlight);\n  }\n\n  void Hide()\n  {\n    mOverlay.HideOverlay();\n  }\n\nprivate:\n  Dali::Ui::AccessibilityHighlightOverlay mOverlay;\n};\n```\n\n## Restore Default Highlight Behavior\n\nAfter using a custom rectangle, call `ResetCustomHighlight()` to return the overlay to its normal highlight calculation. This keeps temporary custom focus visuals from leaking into later accessibility focus changes.\n\n```cpp\nvoid ShowTemporaryCustomHighlight(\n  Dali::Ui::AccessibilityHighlightOverlay& overlay,\n  Dali::Vector2 position,\n  Dali::Vector2 size)\n{\n  overlay.SetCustomHighlight(position, size);\n}\n\nvoid ReturnToDefaultHighlight(Dali::Ui::AccessibilityHighlightOverlay& overlay)\n{\n  overlay.ResetCustomHighlight();\n}\n```\n\nA typical interaction flow is to set a custom rectangle for a specialized view state, then reset it when the view returns to ordinary accessibility focus behavior.\n\n```cpp\nclass CustomHighlightScope\n{\npublic:\n  explicit CustomHighlightScope(Dali::Ui::AccessibilityHighlightOverlay& overlay)\n  : mOverlay(overlay)\n  {\n  }\n\n  void Enter(Dali::Vector2 position, Dali::Vector2 size)\n  {\n    mOverlay.SetCustomHighlight(position, size);\n  }\n\n  void Leave()\n  {\n    mOverlay.ResetCustomHighlight();\n    mOverlay.HideOverlay();\n  }\n\nprivate:\n  Dali::Ui::AccessibilityHighlightOverlay& mOverlay;\n};\n```",
